learning_outcomes.en:
A student who has successfully passed the course:
1) knows and is able to apply central concepts of philosophy of biology;
2) knows the most significant theoretical accounts, arguments and
views in philosophy of biology;
3) knows the main problems of philosophy of biology;
4) is able to provide a critical analysis of main problems and to
(re)construct the main problems in philosophy of biology;
5) is able to express one's knowledge in the field correctly in
writing and oral presentations.
